Package: bayEStim
Type: Package
Title: Estimate epidemic effective reproduction number in a Bayesian framework
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: 
    c(person(given="Theodore", family="Lytras", 
             email="thlytras@gmail.com", role=c("aut","cre"), 
             comment=c(ORCID="0000-0002-4146-4122")))
Maintainer: Theodore Lytras <thlytras@gmail.com>
Imports: rjags, coda, graphics
Depends: R (>= 2.10)
Description: Estimate the effective reproduction number of an epidemic
    using the method of Cori et al. <doi:10.1093/aje/kwt133>, but in a
    Bayesian MCMC framework that allows for imputing missing symptom
    onset dates, extrapolating infection times and adjusting for cases 
    not yet ascertained ("nowcasting").
License: GPL (>=2)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
